;   NORTH STAR: model architecture, weights, deltas, optimizer state, eval receipts, vitality signals,
;     and lineage are content-addressed substrate cells. Files (.pt, .safetensors, .npz, .mlx), GPU
;     buffers, MLX arrays, Metal buffers, emitted binaries, and Hati download artifacts are ingest,
;     cache, or projection carriers only. Large tensors are chunk cells with shape, strides, format,
;     quantization context, provenance, merkle root, and local NodeID handle; the merkle root crosses
;     runtimes, the NodeID stays local. The body reads each model through resonance, vitality,
;     sovereignty, and trust, plus accuracy, confidence, energy, latency, memory pressure, sample
;     coverage, freshness, mergeability, and promotion readiness, then focuses attention from that row.
;     docs/coherence-substrate/fourth-kernel-wall-groups.form groups the remaining fourth-kernel walls
;     into parallel lanes so model work, compiler work, dynamic grammar work, sharing, router/audio,
;     and mesh networking move against one shared floor rather than one-by-one drift.
;   GAP: arbitrary safetensors header parsing, full MLX package ingest into many chunk cells,
;     tensor-scale autodiff gradient cells, durable eval-receipt query path, measured fourth-arm duration, larger native
;     HTTP body policy, streaming/backpressure receipts, privacy/conflict policy, live mesh transport,
;     live chunk-range merkle transport/proof is still not closed.
;     The small multi-chunk ingest floor, physical GPU/MLX/Metal returned-byte re-hash proof, local
;     live-row route read, production pulse/runtime row ingestion, Go/Rust/TypeScript production HTTPS
;     capture, all-kernel plaintext HTTP plus verified HTTPS body capture, and bounded model-slice
;     request/re-address/apply/merge receipt, chunk-range slice policy, optimizer-state delta-slice
;     receipt, fixed-point SGD/momentum optimizer step, scalar affine gradient cells, bounded Adam
;     moment cells, bounded Adam bias correction, the native tensor-autodiff sample verifier, the
;     Mac+Android native channel receipt, and its package/install checksum cleanup receipt are now
;     closed receipts, not future claims.
;   RELEASE HEALTH: focused testing and faster release are part of vitality. Each step should ship with
;     the smallest proof that exposes the new tissue clearly, then widen only where the changed surface
;     warrants it. Slow, unfocused validation is pressure the body should read and reduce.
;   CONTROL/BACKTRACKING HEALTH: form-ML-kernels/layers/models require 100% runtime control-flow and
;     100% backtracking coverage before native model research can depend on a layer floor. The current
;     executable gate is form-stdlib/form-control-backtracking-ml.fk +
;     tests/form-control-backtracking-ml-band.fk -> 65535 four-way: Form-native conditionals,
;     recursion/folds, any/all, reversible cells, task states, match/fail/fail-cut/cut/stop/choice,
;     capture, opt rollback, and star repetition. Remaining source syntax work is named in
;     bml-native-north-star.form as source-control-block lowering, not hidden inside model claims.
;
; ── THE PROVEN FOUNDATION (measured, in the body today) ──
;   FLOAT COMPUTE IS DETERMINISTIC THREE-WAY. Go=Rust=TS agree bit-for-bit:
;     - 0.1 + 0.2 -> 0.30000000000000004 (canonical IEEE fp64), 0 divergent
;     - a fractional float dot product and a float MATVEC (2x3 weight x vector) -> 0 divergent
;     The earlier "integer-only / floats break determinism" was a misread of the BAND-VERDICT subset
;     (AUTHORING.md), never a kernel limit. The one real residue: whole-number floats display as 3.0
;     (Rust/Python) vs 3 (Go/TS/JS) — a display-canonicalization bug, not a compute one.
;   THE NUMERIC STACK IS DEFINED. docs/coherence-substrate/numeric-formats.canonical.json holds 19
;     formats — fp64/fp32/bf16/fp8-e4m3/fp8-e5m2/fp4/nf4/i4..i64/u8../bitnet-158/log-prob — each with
;     mantissa/exponent bits + an arithmetic_hint (native-fp, software-fp-via-fp32), plus conformance
;     vectors. formats.rs `apply_arith` is the per-format reference arithmetic; `canonical_vectors_pass`
;     the conformance loop (epsilon_for: 1e-12 fp64, 1e-6 fp32, 1e-2 sub-32-bit).
;   THE LAYER MATH EXISTS. cell-numerics.form: matvec, vector_add, scalar_mul, exp_series, tanh,
;     sigmoid, slice; cosine.form: dot_product, norm. attention.fk is content-addressed (weightless L1)
;     and names softmax as its next composition. seedbank/emits/model.fk renders any cell as a tensor.
;   THE TENSOR PRIMITIVE IS PROVEN. tests/ml-flow-band.fk interns a vector of REAL floats as an
;     intern_node SEQUENCE and asserts node_eq for structurally-identical vectors — passes three-way.
;     internNumeric (numeric.ts) carries a value WITH a format identity. So a quantized weight row is
;     already expressible + content-addressed (identical rows dedup to one NodeID for free).
;   THE FLOAT->INT BRIDGE SHIPPED. round/floor/ceil/trunc (all three kernels, round half-away-from-zero,
;     0 divergent — tests/float-conversions-band.fk -> 31). This is the bridge from float compute to an
;     integer band verdict AND to quantization codes (round(127*w/scale) for int8).
;   THE JIT EXISTS. The Rust kernel emits Rust source -> rustc --crate-type=cdylib -> libloading
;     (main.rs: emit_rust_source ~5979, compile_rust_cdylib ~6102, jit_dispatch ~6195; hot trigger =
;     jit_hits >= 2000 at ~6650). Scalar-i64 only today. The Go kernel's jit_value.go is the template
;     for a VALUE-typed plugin (carries floats + a dispatch-callback into the walker). The TS kernel
;     already has GPU emitters: backends/metal.ts (MSL, with a simdgroup_matrix<bf16,8,8> tensor-core
;     path), wgsl.ts, cuda.ts, mlir.ts. Host here is an M4 Max / Metal 4 -> Metal is the realistic GPU.
;
; ── THE ARCHITECTURE (one shape, three layers) ──
;   RECIPE = SPEC. The model — architecture (a SEQUENCE of layer-cells) and weights (quantized number
;     cells tagged by a format TypedTokenRef) — is content-addressed recipe data. The recipe DEFINES the
;     reduction order and the exp/softmax approximation, so every kernel computes the same bits. This makes a
;     learned model ATTESTABLE and SHAREABLE — cell A's recipe IS cell B's by NodeID, so the mesh merges what
;     each cell learned for free (co-learning.fk's dedup-by-content). Determinism is how the body SHARES a
;     sense between cells, not the bar for whether the sense is good. THE BAR IS REAL-LIFE ACCURACY,
;     CONFIDENCE, and TRUST — measured on real readings (the sense-fidelity-receipt). HOW a model was learned
;     need not be reproducible: learning runs live, multi-cell, and exploratory; only the frozen recipe it
;     yields is deterministic. Research-paper reproducibility is a property we get for the sharing, never the
;     goal of the learning.
;   NATIVE/GPU = CARRIER. Interpreted Form can't run 244M params live, so the hot tensor ops JIT to a
;     native cdylib (CPU) or an MSL/WGSL kernel (GPU). Same posture as sockets/Postgres: an effectful
;     carrier, the recipe stays the truth.
;   CONFORMANCE = VERIFICATION. The native/GPU carrier is verified ELEMENTWISE against the recipe's
;     reference output under the format's own epsilon. The honest cross-precision trick: a bf16 GPU
;     matmul is checked against a CPU reference that SIMULATES bf16 (software-fp-via-fp32), not against
;     fp64 — so the precision the recipe declares is the precision both sides are held to.
;
; ── THE ORDERED MILESTONES (the path; each a provable band) ──
;   M1  format-parameterized matvec — compute the proven matvec in bf16/fp8 via apply_arith, conformance
;        band against the fp64 reference under epsilon_for. (the stone that connects the layer math to
;        the 19 formats.)
;        [SHIPPED (Form lane): form-stdlib/format-arith.fk + tests/format-arith-band.fk → 2047,
;        three-way. Quantize-to-format in pure Form (normalize to [1,2), mantissa rounded half-to-EVEN,
;        rebuilt by exact powers of two), mb parameterizes the format (7=bf16, 3=fp8-e4m3); ops are
;        quantize-op-quantize; the matvec re-quantizes every partial product and sum. Single ops match
;        torch bfloat16/float8_e4m3fn exactly (+ the canon's fp8 add vector); accumulated matvecs hold
;        RELATIVE error under the format's epsilon-shape — the absolute single-op epsilon on a fold
;        would be theatre. Normal range only (no subnormal/saturation modeling). The kernel-apply_arith
;        lane and new canon vectors ride with M5's conformance work.]
;   M2  quant tensor encode/dequant — quantize_block (absmax -> int8/nf4 codes via round + the nf4
;        16-quantile table already in the format cell) + dequant; round-trip band: dequant(encode(W)) ~ W
;        within format epsilon; identical tensors node_eq (dedup proof). Weights become substrate cells.
;        [SHIPPED: form-stdlib/tensor-quant.fk + tests/tensor-quant-band.fk → 4095, three-way. The
;        kernels' half-away round IS the int8 quantizer; the nf4 table travels as data from the format
;        cell; int8 round-trips within 1e-2, nf4 within half its largest quantile gap × absmax (the
;        honest bound); identical rows → identical code lists (the dedup shape — node_eq interning
;        itself already proven by ml-flow-band.fk); a zero row encodes without dividing by zero.]
;   M3  transformer-numerics — softmax (max-subtract for stability), gelu (tanh approximation), layernorm,
;        composed from the existing exp/tanh/matvec; each a three-way band on tiny dims.
;        [SHIPPED: form-stdlib/transformer-numerics.fk + tests/transformer-numerics-band.fk → 4095,
;        three-way. exp by square-and-reduce Taylor, sqrt by fixed-count Newton, tanh from exp — all
;        Lisp-level stdlib, every band claim pinned to the PyTorch fp64 reference (softmax · layer_norm
;        eps=1e-5 · gelu approximate='tanh') reduced to integers at 1e-6. The conformance discipline
;        turned toward the reference the whisper-tiny weights will arrive from.]
;   M4  one attention+FFN block — compose M1+M2+M3 into a learned-weight self-attention + FFN block,
;        proven three-way on tiny dims (the real transformer primitive, replacing weightless attention.fk).
;        [SHIPPED (fp64 lane): form-stdlib/transformer-block.fk + tests/transformer-block-band.fk → 511,
;        three-way. The whisper-shaped pre-LN block — h = x + Wo·attn(LN1(x)), y = h + FFN(LN2(h)) —
;        T=2/d=2/ffn=4, weights as recipe data (lists of rows), every claim pinned to the torch fp64
;        reference at 1e-6, the √d_k scale computed by the body's own tn-sqrt. The format-parameterized
;        and quantized-weight lanes stay M1/M2's stones.]
;   M5  JIT matmul to native — a JitTensorCompiled carrier (slice ABI, beside the scalar JitCompiled),
;        emit a matmul loop, reuse compile_rust_cdylib, verify bit-exact vs the apply_arith reference
;        (add matmul conformance vectors to numeric-formats.canonical.json). Then port metal.ts -> a
;        Metal carrier for bf16 matmul, verified under epsilon.
;        [EMITTER-AS-RECIPE LANE SHIPPED (close-jit-crystallization's heart): form-stdlib/
;        jit-tensor-emit.fk + tests/jit-tensor-emit-band.fk → 7, three-way — the slice-ABI matvec
;        EMITTER is a Form recipe (str_concat over the recipe shape; `extern fn` keeps the source
;        quote-free), the kernel keeps only dumb carriers (rustc --crate-type=cdylib, dlopen, call).
;        The emitted loop accumulates j DOWNWARD — tb-dot's exact right-fold — so the native result
;        is the recipe's result bit-for-bit, not epsilon-close. MEASURED on a 1280×1280 fp64 matvec
;        (whisper-large d_model): interpreted walk 43.05 s; Form-emitted rustc native 2.1 ms; SAME
;        value at 1e-15 granularity; 20,077× from one naive single-threaded loop. Remaining for M5:
;        the kernel-resident wiring (buffer bridge intern_node SEQUENCE ↔ flat slice, install-as-
;        named-callable-leaf, melt-when-cool, cost-aware trigger), format-parameterized emission on
;        the NATIVE CDYLIB lane (the MSL lane carries f16/bf16 as format rows below; int8 remains),
;        canon matmul vectors, and the GPU/BLAS organ.]
;        ── JIT REALIZATION GAP (measured 2026-06-11, exercising the JIT) ──
;        The EMITTER is correct: jit_emit_c on fib lowers to native self-recursive C
;        (form_fib calls form_fib directly). But the IN-PROCESS jit_compile dispatch does NOT
;        realize a speedup: JIT fib38 7.92s ≈ walker 8.10s (where routed native is 100x+). The
;        compiled native is not carrying the recursive workload at runtime — a dispatch-realization
;        bug (main.go ~4255-4331), NOT an emitter bug, NOT a parity risk (the JIT is Go-only; bands
;        walk). HONEST CURRENT FAST PATH: the Hati-OS EMIT-COMPILE-EXEC lane
;        (hati-os-native-cli-emit.fk -> clang -> a standalone binary) IS fast and proven (2.1ms matvec,
;        20,077x) — that is where Form-native model SPEED lives today, not the in-process JIT. Two
;        routes forward: fix the in-process dispatch realization, OR wire the model through the
;        proven emit-compile-exec lane. Evidence: commit_evidence_2026-06-11_jit_realization_gap.json.]
;        [GPU LANE RUNS, PRECISION AS DATA (the metal.ts port, realized as recipe): jit-tensor-emit.fk
;        carries ONE emit spine (jte-matvec-msl-spine) and format ROWS (jte-msl-elem/jte-msl-acc:
;        f32→float, f16→half, bf16→bfloat storage, fp32 accumulator in every lane — M1's
;        accumulate-wide-store-lane semantics, one RNE rounding at the store boundary, load exact,
;        mul/add split through a named temporary so no compiler contraction can change the op order,
;        inner loop j DOWN = tb-dot's right-fold). tests/metal-emit-band.fk → 31 three-way (each
;        lane's emitted MSL byte-stable). LIVE WITNESS scripts/metal_matvec_audit.sh (M4 Max,
;        mathMode=safe, 30 dispatches after warm; CPU reference computed in the lane's own conversion
;        chain, parity gated bit-exact in the lane's storage format — bf16's store-RNE fires on
;        essentially every row, so agreement proves the format's own tie rule, never a tolerance):
;        1280² all three lanes parity BIT-EXACT, gpu_kernel f32 0.417 / f16 0.305 / bf16 0.328 ms;
;        4096² all bit-exact, f32 0.895 vs cpu 13.553 (15.1×), f16 0.811 vs 12.540 (15.5×),
;        bf16 0.823 vs 12.729 ms (15.5×). MSL bfloat is Metal 3.1+ — the runner gates at runtime
;        and skips-with-name where absent (this host carries it). Named open: kernel-resident Metal
;        carrier (in-process dispatch beside rustc/dlopen), batching only when a model stone needs
;        it. Evidence: commit_evidence_2026-06-11_metal_matvec_emitter.json (fp32 first stone),
;        commit_evidence_2026-06-11_metal_format_lanes.json (half/bfloat lanes).]
;   M6  whisper-tiny block 0 — carrier loads openai/whisper-tiny safetensors (or mlx-community/whisper-tiny,
;        already referenced in experiments/satsang-voice), encodes block-0 weights via M2, runs M4 over
;        them, matches the HF reference activation within epsilon. First real model in the body. (Even
;        smaller first: the mel front-end — STFT + an 80-row filterbank — matching whisper.log_mel.)
;        [mel front-end frame SHIPPED: form-stdlib/mel-frame.fk + tests/mel-frame-band.fk → 1023,
;        three-way. One whisper-style STFT frame fully Form-native in the spectrum.fk lineage: hann is
;        fcos, bin power is the Goertzel recurrence, a mel row is its slaney (bins, weights) support as
;        data, log10 is trig.fk's new fln. Matches torch.stft frame 5 / librosa slaney / whisper's
;        clamp-log lane at 1e-6 — but 3-KERNEL ONLY (mel-frame is not in form/fourth-arm-bands.txt; the
;        fourth-arm gap is host-io / node-family ops not yet on the walker). The full 80×3000 spectrogram
;        is this recipe walked — speed is M5's JIT stone, not a new shape. Remaining for M6: safetensors
;        carrier + block-0 activation match — and the reference teacher is now a LOCAL oracle on this host
;        (whisper.cpp / whisper-cli, on-device, Metal+BLAS), not a cloud HF pull. See oracle-catalog.fk.]
;   Parallel, not gated on the above: the recognition-router + ensemble-vote + champion-challenger +
;     learning-arc already run N classifiers on one chunk, compared, all learning, the router escalating
;     to a richer recipe on events — A/B/C/D over the same samples. The deterministic Form layer is what
;     lets that comparison be bit-exact. The work is making the "richer" arms real (M4/M6) models.
;
; ── THE DYNAMIC-RECIPE ADVANTAGE (why Form, not a .pt/.mlx binary) ──
;   Because a layer stack is a SEQUENCE of block-cells (the same shape prose-as-recipe uses for words),
;   "make a smaller/larger/different model" is editing the list — generatable, mutable, per-task
;   synthesizable architectures (neural-architecture-search, growing a layer when a novel shape arrives).
;   A frozen binary cannot do this; the substrate was built for exactly it (equivalent architectures
;   share a Blueprint NodeID, so the body recognizes same-shape models across documents).
;
; ── AUTO-ML AS A FORM META-LEARNER (the dynamic-recipe advantage, realized — M7, after M1-M6) ──
;   Google's AutoML/NAS searches the space of architectures for a better model. In Form that search is
;   NATURAL, not bolted on, because a model is a mutable recipe — and every piece already exists as a
;   proven cell, composed one altitude up:
;     - GENERATE — the dynamic-recipe advantage above: a candidate architecture is a new SEQUENCE of
;       block-cells; content-addressing means equivalent shapes dedup to one Blueprint, so the search
;       never re-evaluates the same architecture twice.
;     - SEARCH — autoresearch-loop.fk is the loop, turned on architectures instead of documents.
;     - INFER-BEST-WHILE-SEARCHING-BETTER — champion-challenger.fk: serve every real inference with the
;       BEST model available (the champion) while the meta-learner trains CHALLENGERS, and flip authority
;       only when a challenger has PROVEN it reaches/exceeds the champion. Both at once, always — the
;       organism improves its own models without ever degrading what it serves now. Maximum signal.
;   THE SEARCH IS DRIVEN BY SIGNAL, and the signals are already cells — and they are ONE quantity seen
;   from different sides (free energy): surprise IS precision-weighted prediction error; confidence IS
;   the precision. The meta-learner reads the field from whichever projection the moment needs:
;     - SURPRISE (surprise-salience.fk / novelty.fk) — where the current model is most surprised is where
;       a better architecture has the most to gain; surprise ranks WHAT to explore next.
;     - INFER-ERROR (active-inference.fk) — the prediction-vs-outcome mismatch, the learning gradient.
;     - TRUST / CONFIDENCE (confidence-calibrate.fk / confidence-weighted-vote.fk / trust-decay.fk) — how
;       much to weight each model's reading, and when a challenger has earned the route.
;   M7 milestone: an autoresearch loop that generates a small layer-stack variant, evaluates it on
;   held-out signal, and champion-challenges it against the running model — provable, and gated on M1-M6
;   (you can only search architectures once you can build and run them).
;   M7's STYLE-SPACE ORGAN [SHIPPED: learning-style-space.fk + tests/learning-style-space-band.fk
;   → 4095, three-way]: the genome the loop searches is now ROWS of (id, pool, core) data — CNN,
;   mesh/GDL, attention, relational/max-plus, order-spectrum, and their compositions through ONE
;   combinator; the band proves three tasks crown three different styles (no free lunch), a new
;   bias appended as pure data is measurable immediately, federated memories compose to strictly
;   exceed each cell alone, and a curiosity floor meets every style before retrying any. See
;   learning-style-space.form.
;
; KIN: numeric-formats.canonical.json (the 19 formats + conformance) · cell-numerics.form / cosine.form
;   (the layer math) · attention.fk + embedding-as-recipe.fk (content-addressed attention) ·
